B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
FY 2026 Plans:
Continue follow-on development and complete integration of Mission Data Processing Application Provider (MDPAP) application
onto the FORGE Framework for SBIRS ITW/AA data processing. Mission Data Processing Application Framework (MDPAF)
to close out end of FY2025, and Enterprise OPIR Solution (EOS) to be the new contract in place starting FY2026. Complete
final system level integration and testing of mission data processing thrust area (EOS, MDPAP, and Sensor Specific Processing)
for SBIRS transition to operations on FORGE. Further develop the DevSecOps pipeline to be responsive to evolving threats.
Develop and implement plans to integrate Medium Earth Orbit (MEO)/ Low Earth Orbit (LEO) sensor data from MEO Epochs
and Space Development Agency (SDA) Tranches. Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness
necessary to operate in the contested space domain. Activities include, but are not limited to program office support, studies,
technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government
partnership, and international opportunities to respond to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2027 Plans:
Complete integration of FORGE Applications onto the FORGE Framework for SBIRS ITW/AA Strategic Missile Warning data
processing. Complete final system level integration and testing of mission data processing thrust area (EOS, MDPAP, and
SSP) for SBIRS and NGG transition to operations on FORGE. Further develop the DevSecOps pipeline to be responsive to
evolving threats. Implement plans to integrate Medium Earth Orbit (MEO) / Low Earth Orbit (LEO) sensor data from MEO Epochs
and Space Development Agency (SDA) Tranches. Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness
necessary to operate in the contested space domain. Activities include, but are not limited to program office support, studies,
technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction, prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, cloud technologies
U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed
and agility.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The budget for this activity increases in FY2027 to fund the transition of the legacy SBIRS system to the FORGE baseline and
integration of next-generation sensors. The FY2027 budget supports the significant work of completing the final system-level
integration and testing for the Next-Gen GEO (NGG) and proliferated LEO tranche 1 to operations on FORGE.
Title: Next-Gen Transition                                                                                                             176.482      80.048        104.934
Description: Next-Gen transition is the development to enable use of Future Operationally Resilient Ground Evolution (FORGE)
for mission processing and Command and Control (C2) for future Overhead Persistent Infrared (OPIR) space systems. Included in
this effort is the development of Next Gen Interim Ops (NIO) to ensure the most critical ground processing is ready in time for the
first Next-Gen OPIR Geostationary Equatorial Orbit (GEO) satellite launch as required by Joint Requirements Oversight Council
Memorandum (JROCM) 130-17. NIO will create mono tracks and publish those mono tracks to the existing Space Based Infrared
