Description: Overhead Persistent Infrared (OPIR) data collected in space must be relayed to ground entry points and routed
to provide warfighters with timely information. The legacy Space Based Infrared System (SBIRS) ground architecture requires
RGS upgrades and new RGSs to receive OPIR data from legacy and future Next-Gen OPIR assets. This effort expands the RGS
system to two additional sites that will use common hardware capable of supporting all Next Gen-OPIR space assets. This effort
will provide data to the Mission Control Station (MCS) for processing and dissemination to warfighters and National Command
Authorities. The RGS modernization effort will include the ability to operate antennas, process data, and support older Defense
Support Program (DSP) assets. This activity is for RGSs not included in the RGS-A portion of the Future Operationally Resilient
Ground Evolution (FORGE) - RGS architecture. All RGS activities will be consolidated with RGS-A to capture the RGS system as
as an ACAT II program.

FY 2026 Plans:
Complete site specific environmental work and award Task Order for procurement, installation, and test for RGS antennas. Finish
design for support facilities and infrastructure, begin construction of communication shelters, ring walls, and complete installation
of networking and telecommunications equipment.
FY 2027 Plans:
Complete RGS-S and RGS-UK antenna procurement and communication equipment testing. Ship antennas, communication
and cryptological equipment to Schriever SFB and RAF Croughton. Finish RGS-S and RGS-UK design for support facilities and
infrastructure construction of communication shelters and ring walls.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
While initial design and site preparation activities began FY2026, the FY2027 budget is necessary for Facilities and Infrastructure
build out, high-cost procurement of the RGS-S and RGS-UK equipment, and the subsequent shipment of the antennas,
communication, and cryptological equipment to their operational sites.
