Remarks$$, $$Using a Middle Tier Acquisition (MTA), in accordance with DoDI 5000.80, Rapid Prototyping (RP) acquisition pathway approach, GBRD will create a common baseline
for all eight (8) GBRs, and first prototype solutions at four sites before proceeding with Rapid Fielding production for the remaining GBR sites. This strategy enables
agile development and rapid deployment of modernized capabilities. This modernization improves radar weapon system effectiveness and efficiency through increased
commonality, sustainable support, and optimized human interaction, including a digital ecosystem, modular design, and a common baseline.

 The GBRD program will utilize a Fixed Price OTA to execute a gated award process. Gates 1 and 2 will be Firm Fixed Price (FFP) and Gate 3 will be Fixed Price
 Incentive Fee (FPIF). This approach ensures competition, fosters innovation, and provides flexibility to manage risks while delivering critical capabilities. The gated
 process will allow the Government to evaluate Offeror performance and technical maturity through execution, ensuring alignment with program objectives and
 requirements. The following sections provide an overview of the envisioned activities in each Gate and describe the overall framework. Participation in subsequent gates

Operational Systems Development
 will be limited to only Offerors (including subcontractors and Offerors) participating in the previous gate(s). Offerors may update teaming arrangements and cost volume
 for Gate 3 proposal. Teaming to maximize speed and performance and leverage unique skillsets and expertise is highly encouraged.
 The RP phase will encompass up to four GBR sites. There will be an additional proposal after successful completion of Gate 2 for Gate 3's performance. Each
 successful Gate 2 Offeror must propose to all RP sites. RP sites will be awarded to one or more Offerors based on cost, schedule, and performance against program
 requirements. For estimating purposes, Offerors shall assume Gate 3 includes 2x UEWRs (Cape Cod and Clear), PARCS, and COBRA DANE.

