 DCO-S enables Mission Delta 6, cyberspace squadrons, and Joint Force personnel to conduct cyber-integrated space operations that detect, identify, protect against,
 respond to, and recover from malicious threats targeting space mission systems. The program deploys out-of-band (Manticore) and in-band (Kraken) cyber defense
 tool suites to safeguard mission systems supporting critical operations, including Protected Communications, Missile Warning, Military Strategic Communications
 (MILSATCOM), Position Navigation and Timing (PNT), Ballistic Missile Command and Control, Space Domain Awareness (SDA), Nuclear Command Control and
 Communications (NC3), Orbital Warfare, Electronic Warfare, and Command and Control Satellite Operations (C2 Sat Ops).

To address dynamic cyber threats, DCO-S software development must continuously evolve to onboard classified mission systems and integrate new data types beyond
the baseline software. Additionally, the program advances Wide Area Network development to meet security, sustainment, and reach-back requirements for the USSF
Cybersecurity Service Provider, ensuring robust and adaptive cyber defense capabilities for the Space Force.

