Remarks

E. Acquisition Strategy
Space Force will use existing MUOS Capability Production Document (CPD) requirements when developing two operationally similar SLE satellites. On 14 Apr 2022
the program competitively awarded technical and trade studies contracts to three vendors to inform program plans and understanding of required engineering design
changes and potential trades. The Service Acquisition Executive approved the program's acquisition strategy on 14 Sep 2022 as a Major Capability Acquisition pathway,
post-Milestone C program, and the program is executing to plan. On 2 Feb 2024, the program competitively awarded contracts to two vendors for early design and risk
reduction for MUOS SVs 6 and 7. On 26 Nov 2024, the program awarded a follow-on Indefinite-Delivery Indefinite-Quantity (IDIQ) contract to General Dynamics Mission
Systems for ground modernization including the design, production, fielding, and testing of ground updates to ensure availability of the ground segment to 2040. On 31
Jul 2025, the program awarded contract modifications for the two SLE Space Early Design and Risk Reduction vendors, extending the period of performance through
Jan 2026, plus an additional six, one-month options to further satellite design maturity and implement additional risk reduction measures prior to the start of production.
The approved acquisition strategy includes a competitive award between limited sources for the satellite final design and production contract to one vendor in FY 2026.




