C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
begin developing the pathway to rapidly manufacture, integrate, and make available for launch navigation payloads that are
interoperable with existing and future GPS User Equipment.

FY 2026 Plans:
N/A.
FY 2027 Plans:
Initiate technology maturation and risk reduction efforts for new PNT Control segment in order to meet the modern threat
environment and capitalize on advances in commercial technology; develop technical baseline to utilize open interfaces and
MOSA to enable enduring, multi-vendor competition and plug-and-play development; achieve contract ATP; manage cost,
schedule, and performance of numerous vendors for control segment development. Initiate efforts to mature technology for
increased resiliency and availability across future GPS Segments (Ground, Space, and User Equipment).

Rapidly respond to implement system resiliency and situational awareness necessary to operate in the contested space domain.
Activities may include, but are not limited to program office support, studies, technical analysis, experimentation, risk reduction,
prototyping, and activities that may leverage commercial, U.S. Government partnership, and international opportunities to respond
to existing and emerging adversarial threats with speed and agility.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY27 funding increased due to FY27 being first year of funding.
