INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$1207440SF$$, 2027, $$Autonomous Tactical Fabric (ATF) delivers "Space Operations of the Future” by fundamentally changing how Guardians interact with the battlespace. ATF consists of
transformational Infrastructure Modernization to create a deliberate, resilient architecture where physical location does not limit space operations, Fabric to enable cross-
mission data accessibility for autonomy and analytics, and Mission Operations where health and status data integrates with the Fabric along with path-independent
communication for Fleet Operations and Artificial Intelligence (AI)/Machine Learning (ML) is applied to reduce repetitive functions and data overload while implementing.
Additionally, Integration will perform the technical, hands-on integration needed to connect intra-program technical areas as well as USSF and DAF stakeholders to the
Infrastructure and Fabric. ATF will enable future Space Force operations to be conducted from diverse locations, using any sensor or system, while also autonomously
harmonizing data across various echelons at speed and scale. ATF will increase resilience, automation, and connectivity to operate throughout the conflict spectrum
by creating an ecosystem for weapon systems to connect in order to share data needed to elevate decisions. The program will implement autonomous sensor
orchestration, path-agnostic meshed networking, and a common, shared, distributed data plane to fundamentally pivot space operations with next generation of software
to accelerate decision making. ATF is not replacing existing programs or projects, but building the underlying ecosystem and framework needed to interconnect systems
and data.

USSF Space Systems Command is developing the Autonomous Tactical Fabric for Guardians across warfighting, ops commands, and combat support organizations. As
a result, the Service will improve battle management of all weapon systems; deliver SDA capabilities; and deter, neutralize, defeat and/or destroy counterspace threats
and defend the homeland; and continue to advance all near term effects.

This program falls within the Space Domain Awareness (SDA) mission area which provides the space-based and ground-based architecture required to detect, track,
catalogue, and identify objects and activities in the space domain. As the foundation for space control, SDA encompasses surveillance of all space objects and activities;
detailed surveillance of specific space assets; monitoring space environmental conditions; monitoring cooperative space assets; gathering indications and warning
on adversary space operations; and conducting integrated command, control, communications, processing, analysis, dissemination, and archiving activities. Space

Operational Systems Development
 Force investment program interdependencies include: RDT&E Budget Line Items: Space Domain Awareness/Planning/Tasking SW (1208248SF); Space Situational
 Awareness Operations (1203940SF); Space Situational Awareness Systems (1206425SF); and elements of Procurement Budget Line Item: Space Mods (SPCMOD).

This program element may include necessary civilian pay expenses required to manage, execute, and deliver weapon system capability. The use of such program funds
would be in addition to the civilian pay expenses budgeted in program elements 1206392SF and 1206398SF.

This program is in Budget Activity 7, Operational System Development because this budget activity includes development efforts to upgrade systems that have been
