C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Infrastructure Modernization                                                                                                             -           -        932.680
Description: Infrastructure Modernization is the foundation to enable speed and scale and capitalize on commercial
advancements, such as AI/ML technologies. It will enable multiple systems together to achieve autonomy at various levels of
operations. It will address critical gaps in infrastructure, fund the compute and storage environment needed to transition USSF
Weapon Systems to a cognitive mission fabric for automation and cross-mission data sharing, and create a resilient architecture
where physical location does not limit space operations.

FY 2027 Plans:
Initiate infrastructure work (i.e., physical infrastructure, power, cooling, etc.) needed to establish an ecosystem for distributed,
resilient operations. Buy hardware as needed to support the initialization of the infrastructure. Begin assessment of workload

Operational Systems Development

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
requirements (i.e., compute and storage) needed by mission areas and to host a cognitive mission fabric to synchronize USSF
weapon systems at various echelons.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increase of 932.680 million due to being a new start.
Title: Fabric                                                                                                                                   -              -      369.600
Description: The Fabric creates a common, defined, consistent operating system to maximize data sharing by unifying and
integrating any sensor to any effector via any transport. A key component of the Fabric is the cognitive mission fabric, where
mission system data is abstracted and sent to a distributed software component to expose data needed to enable decision-
making with human in/on the loop leveraging advanced Human Machine Interfaces/Human Machine Teaming. This is imperative
to capitalize on AI/ML to offload data curation/assessment and data overload and allow human operators to focus on situational
understanding of the battlespace and develop Courses of Action. Edge nodes will be used for forward data processing, while
space ops edge nodes will be used to implement a "Follow the Sun” operational construct to share the cognitive load and
operational burden across the globe. The Fabric will include multiple network types and nodes, such as terrestrial and space-
based, for data transport to ultimately connect any weapon systems at any classification levels to the Fabric and Infrastructure
to significantly increase resiliency and redundancy. It will also serve as the foundation for cyber defense and optimize sharing of
critical wartime data by integrating commercial systems and data from Allies and Partners.

FY 2027 Plans:
Award the cognitive mission fabric contract and begin integration with the infrastructure. Operationalize initial interface abstraction
prototype capabilities for the SDA mission. Purchase and install long lead hardware items for the network nodes to connect the
Infrastructure and Fabric and enable a cross-mission communication and data sharing.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increase of 369.600 million due to being a new start.
Title: Mission Operations                                                                                                                       -              -      113.300
Description: Mission Operations integrates mission specific health and status data with the Fabric and applies AI/ML to reduce
repetitive functions and data overload, while increasing situational understanding of kill chain execution. Provides access to
additional antenna capacity and path-independent communication for Fleet Operations. It will mature and integrate AI/ML tools
and technologies that are compatible with mission specific software to optimize alerting and cross-mission information sharing,
with the goal of automating routine tasks and allowing the operators to focus on the battlespace.

FY 2027 Plans:

Operational Systems Development

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                         FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
Prototype tool and technologies to expedite integration of mission specific operations data onto the Fabric, which includes satellite
and payload health and status information as well as ground-based sensor data. Demonstrate operational function of AI/ML
technologies to reduce repetitive functions needed to eliminate data overload. Modify antenna interfaces to integrate with the
USSF antenna orchestrator.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increase of 113.300 million due to being a new start
Title: Integration                                                                                                                                -              -      108.720
Description: Performs the technical, hands-on integration needed to connect the program's systems and link USSF and
Department of the Air Force stakeholders to the Infrastructure and Fabric. It will integrate the cognitive mission fabric onto the
Infrastructure (i.e. cloud) as well as any additional network connectivity needed to enable the distributed cognitive mission fabric
and data exposure across the Department. This thrust is also responsible for identifying the unique interfaces needed to expose
key information from each Space Force mission area needed to expedite decisions and performing the technical analysis and
integration to make the data available to the Fabric.

FY 2027 Plans:
Begin integration of networks with the infrastructure. Begin integration of initial interface abstraction prototype capabilities into the
Fabric. Begin technical planning and integration for mission specific data fortwo mission areas.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increase of 108.730 million due to being a new start.
