Remarks$$, $$The Automated Tactical Fabric program will prioritize commercial integration over development and initiate major development activities as a last resort to meeting
noncommercially-available needs. The program is planning to execute a hybrid acquisition strategy leveraging Middle Tier of Acquisition (MTA) authority for Rapid
Prototyping and Fielding, a Public/Private Partnership, and Commercial Solutions Opening.

To support this acquisition strategy, the program is pursuing a rapid prototyping approach founded primarily on the integration of commercial software, a private/public
partnership for the storage and compute solution, and expanding and iterating existing acquisitions to include existing contracts where necessary, while maximizing the

Operational Systems Development
 use of two solutions in the architecture where possible. For the Infrastructure Modernization thrust, the ATF program plans to use a Commercial Solutions Opening with
 a private/public partnership to acquire storage and compute solutions needed for large scale modernization. For the Fabric and Mission Operations thrusts, ATF will
 use a combination of Commercial Solutions Openings and existing contracts, leveraging incentive mechanisms appropriate to the contract. Integration of ATF will be
 performed by a Lead System Integrator who will perform technical integration, working across USSF to integrate systems and data with the Fabric.

