to capitalize on AI/ML to offload data curation/assessment and data overload and allow human operators to focus on situational
understanding of the battlespace and develop Courses of Action. Edge nodes will be used for forward data processing, while
space ops edge nodes will be used to implement a "Follow the Sun” operational construct to share the cognitive load and
operational burden across the globe. The Fabric will include multiple network types and nodes, such as terrestrial and space-
based, for data transport to ultimately connect any weapon systems at any classification levels to the Fabric and Infrastructure
to significantly increase resiliency and redundancy. It will also serve as the foundation for cyber defense and optimize sharing of
critical wartime data by integrating commercial systems and data from Allies and Partners.

FY 2027 Plans:
Award the cognitive mission fabric contract and begin integration with the infrastructure. Operationalize initial interface abstraction
prototype capabilities for the SDA mission. Purchase and install long lead hardware items for the network nodes to connect the
Infrastructure and Fabric and enable a cross-mission communication and data sharing.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
FY 2027 increase of 369.600 million due to being a new start.
Title: Mission Operations                                                                                                                       -              -      113.300
Description: Mission Operations integrates mission specific health and status data with the Fabric and applies AI/ML to reduce
repetitive functions and data overload, while increasing situational understanding of kill chain execution. Provides access to
additional antenna capacity and path-independent communication for Fleet Operations. It will mature and integrate AI/ML tools
and technologies that are compatible with mission specific software to optimize alerting and cross-mission information sharing,
with the goal of automating routine tasks and allowing the operators to focus on the battlespace.

