INSERT INTO public.pe_narratives (pe_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, accomplishments, planned_program, performance_metrics, other_program_funding, raw_text, content_hash, section_hashes, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$1208053SF$$, 2027, $$Detachments 1 through 4 are operating the Joint Tactical Ground Station (JTAGS) (Project 676760) WT-5 systems for Guardians across Missile Warning and Missile
Tracking (MW/MT) mission area. As a result, the Service will improve readiness and operational reach of existing force structure.

 JTAGS is a post-production, Acquisition Category (ACAT) III program. The weapon system designator for JTAGS is WT-5. JTAGS provides missile warning message
 data for the Air and Missile Defense (AMD) architecture. JTAGS disseminates near real time warning, alerting, and cueing information on ballistic missile launches and
 events of interest throughout the theater using existing communication networks, providing critical support to Combatant Commanders in their Areas of Responsibility
 (AOR). Additionally, JTAGS supports the Strategic Missile Warning architecture. JTAGS consist of two sheltered operation rooms, one equipment room, and three
 antennas. Four outside contiguous United States (OCONUS) deployed JTAGS units, which are deployed in three theaters (United States Pacific Command (PACOM),
 United States Central Command (CENTCOM), United States European Command (EUCOM)), constitute Department of War's (DoW) in-theater system providing
 space-based missile warning. The fifth contiguous United States (CONUS) system is used as an institutional trainer but is available as a deployable asset. JTAGS is
 designated as the in-theater element of the United States Strategic Command's Theater Event System (TES), supporting all Theater Missile Defense pillars, affording
 the shortest sensor-to-shooter connectivity. The JTAGS Block II P3I program based on the 2009 JTAGS ORD is on contract as a two-phase development effort. Joint
 Requirements Oversight Council (JROC) Memos 197-12, 113-13, and 042-19 and PL 111-383 support the requirements to develop and field JTAGS Block II capabilities
 as soon as possible.

 Continued JTAGS Block II CDD addresses evolving User-driven needs such as emerging threats, resiliency, modernization, and expanding interfaces that were not
 known at the time the JTAGS ORD was validated. Developmental efforts to achieve JTAGS Block II CDD threshold requirements continue through FY 2032.

 Resilient Ground Architecture establishes a proliferated missile warning processing & data distribution ground architecture that holistically creates a robust day-to-
 day operation with predictable and graceful degradation to a Survivable & Endurable mission—providing increased resilience through all phases of conflict and threat
 spectrum. Fielding RGA capabilities meets/aligns with JROC-M 059-23, PPD-35/40, and CJCSI 3296. Resilient Ground Architecture is a new start with efforts beginning
 in FY 2027.
 Note that Resilient Ground Architecture funding is split between PE 1208053SF and PE 1206440SF.

