N/A
FY 2027 Base Plans:
Begin upgrade of the current JTAGS infrastructure. These upgrades both increase today's JTAGS site resiliency
against jamming and cyber threats above and beyond Block II compliance activities, and lay the foundation
for future capabilities such as next gen/ Resilient MWT Medium Earth Orbit (MEO) sensor processing, SMW
mission failover from Mission Control Station( MCS), and cross-command TMW. The projects increase data
pub/sub between JTAGS and RTS, begin replacement of SAGE with FORGE, and begin upgrade of the JTAGS
DDL comms architecture. Additional upgrades include beginning connection of JTAGS sites to SMW- supporting
Ground Entry Point (GEP) infrastructure (Relay Ground Stations (RGS) for Space Based Infrared System/Next
Gen Geosynchronous (SBIRS/NGG), Medium Earth Orbit (MEO) GEPs), beginning upgrade of JTAGS front-
end processing hardware to ingest data from new sources, and beginning integration of new back-end comms to
push SMW messages to strategic users.

Also, begin the mesh network connectivity between MCS, JTAGS, and existing GEP infrastructure to ensure
high availability of SMW mission data at OCONUS failover locations.
