Remarks
The Joint Tactical Ground Station (JTAGS) transitioned to US Space Force in FY2024.$$, $$This program element develops critical software intensive improvements, while continuing to make maximum use of Non-Developmental Items (NDI)/Commercial Off-
The-Shelf (COTS) components and Government Furnished Equipment (GFE). After design and integration, the system will be subject to thorough developmental and
validation/verification testing to verify performance, operational effectiveness and suitability. The JTAGS Block II Pre-planned Product Improvement (P3I) program was
initiated based on a 2009 JTAGS Operational Requirements Document (ORD) and upgrades JTAGS to a Block II configuration for operation with the next generation
of Space Based Infrared System (SBIRS) satellites, improving warning tactical parameters and timeliness. The JTAGS Block II P3I contract was a full and open
competition, but only the incumbent JTAGS contractor submitted a proposal, resulting in a sole-source contract on 26 Aug 2012. The contract's development options
are Cost Plus Incentive Fee; its production options are Firm Fixed Price, and its Sustainment options are Cost Plus Fixed Fee. The JTAGS Block II contract's period of
performance is from 1 October 2012 through 30 September 2021 with a contract extension to March 2022. As threats continued to evolve and change as well as new
satellite sensors became available, the JTAGS Users in conjunction with the Army Capabilities Manager developed a JTAGS Block II Capability Development Document
(CDD), requiring JTAGS to address new/changing threats that were not addressed in the 2009 JTAGS ORD. The acquisition of the continued JTAGS Block II efforts
based on the JTAGS Block II CDD was performed under a sole source follow-on contract awarded May 2022 to the current JTAGS contractor with an expiration of Dec
2024. The JTAGS Block II P3I contract was extended by 6 months to allow for a new contract to be put in place with a period of performance expiring 30 June 2030.
This new contract accommodates continuity of support as JTAGS undergoes resiliency and modernization upgrades. The scope of work will continue to focus on Block
II Capability Development, addressing new/changing threats, research and develop prototypes/proof of concepts and the incorporation of resiliency/next generation
capabilities into the weapon system architecture.

 Resilient Ground Architecture establishes a proliferated missile warning processing & data distribution ground architecture that will have a robust day-to- day operation
 with predictable and graceful degradation to a Survivable & Endurable mission; providing increased resilience through all phases of conflict and threat spectrum. Fielding
 RGA capabilities meets/aligns with JROC-M 059-23, PPD-35/40, and CJCSI 3296. RGA will heavily leverage the existing JTAGS contracts for JTAGS RGA efforts.

