A. Mission Description and Budget Item Justification
This is not a new start. Funding was transferred from the Space Domain Awareness (SDA) C2 in Project 68A035 of this Program Element to the Kronos Project 681018
and substantially enhanced for a total of 260.441 million in FY 2027 to expand development of Battle Management and C2 scope previously in SDA. This is consistent
with the direction and intent of the Under Secretary of War for Acquisition and Sustainment in splitting the Space Domain Awareness (SDA) and BMC2 programs out of
the Space C2 program as documented in a 12 May 2025 Acquisition Decision Memorandum.

 The Kronos program (Project 681018) is developing the U.S. Space Force's modern software suite for space operations command and control (C2), battle management,
 and space intelligence integration. It replaces legacy tools with a modular, data-driven, and integrated family of systems that helps operators plan, task, deconflict,
 execute, and assess space operations in a contested and dynamic environment. Kronos provides capabilities across the BMC2 family of systems to exercise the
 authority and direction by a commander over assigned/attached forces to accomplish the mission. The four major activities include: planning, preparing, executing,
 and assessing. Continuing efforts support Space Planning by matching combat resources to effects to improve the ability to synthesize guidance, effects, and priorities
 with available resources to plan, generate, coordinate and execute combined fires between operational and tactical units. Lastly, these capabilities enable decision
 advantage for joint and coalition forces by integrating space intelligence throughout BMC2 processes to enable space superiority. This is the USSF BMC2 program that
 directly supports the Department of the Air Force (DAF) Portfolio Acquisition Executive (PAE) for Command, Control, Communications and Battle Management (C3BM)
 to enable joint all-domain operations.

 Space Systems Command (SSC) System Delta (SYD) 85 and the Kronos Program Office are continuing to develop the Kronos Family of Systems for Guardians
 across Warfighting, Operational Command, and Combat Support units. As a result, the Service will improve battle management of all weapon systems and adjust force
 structure as required.

