D. Acquisition Strategy
The Space Domain Awareness (SDA) Atlas software program is employing agile software development practices in the Software Acquisition Pathway (SWP), in
accordance with the approved June 2024 Acquisition Strategy Document. In FY 2025 the Atlas program began performing in the Execution phase of the SWP. A
Software Initial Capabilities Document (SW ICD) provides requirements which serve as a top-level Work Breakdown Structure (WBS) for the program. The program
acquires tools and capabilities through an agile-based Rapid Delivery Framework that delivers and sustains new features and capabilities through a Continuous
Integration / Continuous Delivery pipeline with 120-day Program Increments. The program's acquisition strategy gains efficiencies as a Software and Digital Technology
Pilot as it develops and sustains platform and data services and software applications. This strategy focuses on rapidly delivering capability to warfighters and
leveraging commercial, industry and government partners. Currently there are multiple contractors performing on competitively awarded and sole-source contracts with
no single prime contractor responsible for the entire ecosystem.




