B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                 FY 2025           FY 2026        FY 2027
Title: 5G Technology                                                                                                                    1.500                -              -
Description: DISA will conduct a comprehensive initiative to assess the demand and plan for the deployment of a
Defense Information System Network (DISN) hosted enterprise 5G private core network to enhance Department of War
(DoW )communications capabilities. Input from DoW Combatant Commands, Services, and Agencies will determine future
Department-wide implementation. Explore 5G device anonymization mobile technologies to enhance user privacy while operating
on standard cellular services, both domestically and internationally.

Developed a detailed deployment plan, which will include recommending a technical solution that adheres to 3rd Generation
Partnership Project (3GPP) standards and the evolving DoW 5G Reference Architecture, along with evaluating alternative
solutions.
Provided a final report and briefing to the Department of War Chief Information Office (DoW CIO) 5G Cross-Functional (CFT) team
that offers a comprehensive strategy for the network's implementation, security, and scalability across the DoW enterprise.
Developed an initial cost estimate and resourcing strategy will be provided to DoW CIO to determine future resourcing and funding
requirements based on mission demand and feedback.
Tested and evaluated Mobile Device Anonymization devices and technologies that help protect user privacy when operating on
standard cellular services both domestically and internationally.

Based on the initial 5G private core demand assessment conducted by DISA in support of the DoW CIO, feedback from the DoW
Combatant Commands, Services, and Agencies revealed that several entities have already implemented their own 5G private
core networks. The DoW CIO has determined that no additional funding is required for FY26 and beyond.

