B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025           FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: Automation Technical Integration and Engineering in Cyberspace                                                                        1.726             1.403       1.566
Description: This program provides research and development, conducts technology assessments, and provides data to drive
real time automation integration decisions and enterprise solutions, ultimately improving the user experience. As DISA moves
towards a shared transparency of understanding, automation of technical solutions promotes increased information sharing
and improved understanding of interdependencies underlying service operations and mission activities. Emerging information
technology must support the current and next-generation warfighters to ensure systems are protected while also leveraging
advances in automation to deliver capabilities. Ultimately, these efforts support the achievement of an optimized IT environment to
protect against threats in cyberspace that remain dynamic and persistent.

FY 2026 Plans:
Integrate advanced AI/ML-driven automation for proactive threat detection, response, and anomaly mitigation across various
enterprise platforms.
FY 2027 Plans:

                                                                                 ty Program

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027
• Continue migration efforts and associated Test and Evaluation Efforts required to migrate the DoW PKI to a hybrid cloud
environment, addressing emerging requirements (like Global Gray and SIPR mobile credentialing) and reducing operational costs.
• Conduct targeted cyber assessments of high-priority emerging technologies.
• Collaborate with mission partners and industry to validate new automation technologies through operational pilot programs and
limited production deployments
• Advance the implementation of real-time automation and orchestration technologies to support dynamic cyberspace operations
and reduce manual response time across enterprise environments.
• Develop and pilot AI/ML-enabled automation frameworks that support predictive analytics and proactive system remediation in
support of cyber defense missions.
• Conduct enterprise-wide assessments to identify and prioritize automation opportunities in IT service management (ITSM),
cybersecurity, and network operations.
• Expand integration of automated solutions across operational domains to improve situational awareness, streamline workflows,
and enhance end-user experience.
• Collaborate with mission partners and industry to validate new automation technologies through operational pilot programs and
limited production deployments.
• Guide agency automation integration activities for improved service operations impacting user experience in cyberspace.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The increase of +$0.163 million from FY 2026 and FY 2027 supports expanded research, pilot deployments, and development of
AI/ML-enabled automation capabilities. These investments will accelerate real-time automation adoption, support enterprise-wide
technical assessments, and drive improved efficiency and effectiveness in cyberspace operations.
Increase also supports changes in contract costs.
Title: Zero Trust Architecture (ZTA)                                                                                                      0.000       2.086         2.136
Description: The ZTA project supports the effort to create a Zero Trust Commercial Cloud Lab (ZTCCL). The ZTCCL is an
environment that provides an integration space to develop, test, and mature concepts, capabilities, and technology to benefit the
DoW Information Network (DoWIN). These concepts, capabilities, and technologies will increase the DoWIN’s ability to prevent,
detect, respond, and recover from malicious cyber activities while proving scalability to enterprise levels.

The ZTCCL will:
• Provide a test and development environment to test ZT capabilities within a cloud lab environment.
• Provide automations for customer research and development with an activity template to include standard IT domain builds,
three tiered applications that improve scalability and availability, and "Gold images" that provide a consistent system baseline for
common Operating Systems deployments.

                                                                                ty Program

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                 FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027

The ZT project stemmed from a FY 2018 initial Zero Trust Reference Architecture effort with US Cyber Command, NSA, and
DoW-CIO.

FY 2026 Plans:
Funding provides cybersecurity testing activities to maintain accreditation and Authority-To-Operate (ATO) approvals to maintain
ZTA Operational Status and Mission Capability Readiness. Additionally, funds provide integration and operational testing of
new or updated hardware/software versions to ensure evolution, interoperability, and operational readiness of deployed ZTA
capabilities.
FY 2027 Plans:
Funding continues to provide Cybersecurity testing activities to maintain accreditation and Authority-To-Operate (ATO) approvals
to maintain ZTA Operational Status and Mission Capability Readiness. Additionally, funds provide integration and operational
testing of new or updated hardware/software versions to ensure evolution, interoperability, and operational readiness of deployed
ZTA capabilities.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The increase of +$0.050 million from FY 2026 and FY 2027 for ZT is attributed to changes in cost contracts.
Title: Public Key Infrastructure (PKI)                                                                                                 6.907      19.735        29.800
Description: Provide non-reputable digital identities of users, devices, applications, and services for both DoW and external
mission partners using hardware and software-based certificate/key pairs, and a suite of capabilities that uses interoperable
industry standards (OCSP/CRLs) to enable real-time revocation status of those identities. Enable secure communication at OSI
5/6.

FY 2026 Plans:
Public Key Infrastructure: RDT&E funding will support integration testing of key PKI Technical Capabilities as directed/mandated
by the DoW CIO for continued evolution of the DoW PKI Infrastructure Cryptographic Algorithm. Additional funding will continue
PKI Modernization Development, Integration, Performance.

Cryptographic Modernization (Algorithm Evolution): Funding is needed to transition the DoW PKI to stronger cryptographic
algorithms (RSA 3072/4096 and SHA-384) by the 2027 deadline, ensuring compliance with NSA standards and enhanced
security. This involves building and testing the infrastructure to support these new algorithms across various environments
(Development, O&M, test, and production).

                                                                                ty Program

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027
PKI Modernization (Hybrid Cloud Platform): RDT&E is required to migrate the DoW PKI to a hybrid cloud environment, addressing
emerging requirements (like Global Gray and SIPR mobile credentialing) and reducing operational costs. This includes testing
the platform with the NSA, updating PKI policies, and migrating existing systems to the new modernized platform. The current
infrastructure only supports sustainment and lacks the flexibility for modernization.

DoW PKI Public Trust: Funding will establish and sustain a Public Trust Certificate Authority, enabling automated issuance and
renewal of publicly trusted TLS certificates for DoW and Federal Government systems. This will ensure that visitors trust the
confidentiality of their communications with these systems without requiring government-specific trust chains.
FY 2027 Plans:
Public Key Infrastructure: RDT&E funding will continue integration testing of key PKI Technical Capabilities as directed/mandated
by the DoW CIO for continued evolution of the DoW PKI Infrastructure Cryptographic Algorithm. Additional funding will continue
PKI Modernization Development, Integration, Performance.

Funds will also support critical Cryptographic Modernization (Algorithm Evolution) to transition the DoW PKI to stronger
cryptographic algorithms (RSA 3072/4096 and SHA-384) by the 2027 deadline, ensuring compliance with NSA standards
and enhanced security. This involves building and testing the infrastructure to support these new algorithms across various
environments (Development, O&M, test, and production). This will include investigating alternative PKI solutions.

PKI Modernization (Hybrid Cloud Platform): RDT&E Funds will continue migration efforts and associated Test and Evaluation
Efforts required to migrate the DoW PKI to a hybrid cloud environment, addressing emerging requirements (like Global Gray and
SIPR mobile credentialing) and reducing operational costs. This includes testing the platform with the NSA, updating PKI policies,
and migrating existing systems to the new modernized platform. The current infrastructure only supports sustainment and lacks
the flexibility for modernization.

DoW PKI Public Trust: RDT&E Funds will continue Sustainment of a Public Trust Certificate Authority, enabling automated
issuance and renewal of publicly trusted TLS certificates for DoW and Federal Government systems. This will ensure that visitors
trust the confidentiality of their communications with these systems without requiring government-specific trust chains.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The increase of +$10.065 million from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is attributed to increased RDT&E requirements for continued
requirements to align with the Department of War's (DoW) Strategic Objectives for modernizing its Cryptographic Infrastructure.
Increase is also attributed to continued PKI Modernization Efforts that will provide a Hybrid Cloud Environment that provides

                                                                                 ty Program

