0400: Research, Development, Test & Evaluation, Defense-Wide / BA 7:          PE 0303140K / Information Systems Security Program
Operational Systems Development
       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2025 funding decrease is due to the realignment of funds to O&M for the purchase of MDE/ MDI licenses that deliver capabilities for meeting Zero Trust.
       Implementation accelerates and enhances DoWs cybersecurity posture and its ability to reach Target Level Zero Trust in accordance with the DoD Zero Trust
       Strategy dated 21 Oct 2022. The DoD Zero Trust Mandate: The Department of War has initiated a sweeping cybersecurity overhaul known as the Zero Trust
       Strategy. The Strategy, dated 10/21/2021, moves away from the traditional to a perimeter defense to a modern data-centric security model built on the principle
       of “never trust, always verify” aka Zero Trust. DoW set an aggressive timeline mandating all components achieve “Target Level Zero Trust” by end of FY27.

       The FY 2026 President’s Budget submission did not include FY 2027 funding projections. Therefore, no comparison between budget positions is available for FY
       2027.




