 Information Technology (EMS IT) modernization, consolidating these spectrum tools and capabilities into a single artificial intelligence-enabled platform – Maven Smart
 Systems (MSS). MSS is a comprehensive, Software as a Service-based enterprise data operating system designed to integrate, manage, and analyze data from
 disparate sources in support of U.S. military operations. MSS serves as a central hub connecting raw data, analytics, and artificial intelligence/machine learning models
 to real-world military operations. The initial work in FY 2027 will focus on migrating DISA-owned capabilities, with an emphasis on EMBM-J.

 EMS IT modernization will replace legacy spectrum management capabilities and apply automation and artificial intelligence to enable joint force commanders to
 coordinate, synchronize, and integrate the use of EMS across the full range of military operations, by providing robust and integrated spectrum management, Situational
 Awareness (SA), Command and Control (C2), and Decision Support (DS). Further, by transforming the EMS into a truly agile, resilient, and intelligently managed
 domain, EMS IT Modernization will provide the critical EMS end-to-end data layer for CJADC2, enabling the rapid, secure, and uninterrupted flow of information
 necessary for decision advantage to achieve EMS superiority in any conflict.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                        FY 2025          FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: Electromagnetic Spectrum Information Technology (EMS IT) Modernization (includes Electromagnetic Battle Management-                    14.937           15.674      48.825
Joint (EMBM-J) Transition and Upgrade)
Description: EMS IT modernization will migrate existing spectrum tools and capabilities to a single, modernized platform built on
a dynamic architecture with common data standards: Maven Smart Systems (MSS). This will enable near real-time processing,
support artificial intelligence and machine learning, and allow for the rapid deployment and standardization of EMS IT services.
By consolidating these functions, the Department will be able to conduct the full range of joint planning, coordination, and control
activities for Joint Electromagnetic Spectrum Operations, as outlined in Joint Publication 3-85 and the Joint Electromagnetic
Spectrum Operations Cell Operational Employment Guide.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027
As part of this effort, DISA will move the Electromagnetic Battle Management-Joint (EMBM-J) to the common platform and
continuously enhance EMBM-J to meet warfighter needs. EMBM-J enables the Joint Force Commander to dynamically plan,
direct, monitor, and assess EMS usage across four primary areas:

• Situational Awareness (SA): Combines and correlates previously stove piped data sources (Intel, EMS management,
Electromagnetic Warfare; positional data); provides spectrum activity and pattern of life, data analytics, and analysis.
• Decision Support (DS): Automates EMS joint planning through integration of electromagnetic order of battle, spectrum
dependent system parametric data, and planning information to enable users to model and simulate courses of action based on
projected electromagnetic spectrum operating environment and the Commander's intent.
• Command and Control (C2): Provides ability to command and control within the EMS, interoperability between global and local
common operating pictures and Service capabilities, and operations in a disconnected/limited bandwidth environment.
• Training: Connects with Joint Live, Virtual, and Constructive environments, generates scalable training scenarios, and integrates
into major Joint Force exercises.

FY 2026 Plans:
In FY 2026, DISA is continuing to develop the EMBM-J mission capability in support of DoW's Electromagnetic Spectrum
Strategy.
• Continue rapid software releases to expand and enhance situational awareness and the EMS Joint Planning processes by
providing additional data, automation, and functionality.
FY 2027 Plans:
In FY 2027, DISA is embarking on EMS IT Modernization to create a common artificial intelligence-enabled platform for Spectrum
tools and capabilities – Maven Smart Systems (MSS). Modernization will include the following activities:
• Transition EMBM-J functionality (SA, DS, C2) into MSS common data integrator and automation platform on Impact Level (IL)-6.
• Initiate development of legacy spectrum management / frequency assignment functions (SXXI) into the MSS common data
integrator and automation platform on IL-6.
• Initiate expansion of EMS functionality into Top Secret environments, including respective cross domain integration.
• Initiate extension of EMS functionality to one Joint Operational Edge (JOE) node to enable Denied, Degraded, Intermittent, and
Limited (DDIL) operations.
• Integration of artificial intelligence/machine learning for EMS functions to include EMBM-J functionality (SA, DS, C2) and
spectrum management.

DISA will also continue enhancing EMBM-J mission capability through agile/iterative releases to:

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                     FY 2025    FY 2026      FY 2027
• Begin automating Command and Control (C2) and interoperability between Joint and electromagnetic spectrum operations
tools to streamline electromagnetic spectrum operations requirements through established Joint and Component-level chains of
command critical to mission planning / execution.
• Fuse additional EMS mission datasets, automate the development and analysis of the electromagnetic order of battle,
electromagnetic operating environment, and advanced EMS modeling and simulation.
• Incorporate artificial intelligence to support ingestion and generation of electromagnetic spectrum operations planning and
execution orders.

EMS IT Modernization is occurring in direct coordination with DoW CIO, Joint Staff J6, Chief Data and Artificial Intelligence Officer
(CDAO) and Electromagnetic Spectrum Steering Group (EMS SSG).
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The increase of +$33.151 million from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is for EMS IT modernization. DISA is migrating EMBM-J and other
legacy capabilities to a single platform and data integrator, Maven Smart Systems (MSS), and expanding to one Joint Operational
Edge (JOE) cloud node for resiliency. EMS IT modernization will optimize spectrum management, frequency allocation, and EMS
operations.
