B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                      FY 2025           FY 2026     FY 2027
Title: JRICM Study                                                                                                                           0.700             1.444       1.589
Description: Joint Regional Integrated Air and Defense Capability Mix (JRICM) will use analysis of adversary advanced ballistic,
cruise, and hypersonic missile capabilities to determine if a layered missile defense can successfully degrade or defeat adversary
missile attacks to extend defense duration in support of the Golden Dome for America. Funding will enable the study to proceed
with support from the various government organizations and FFRDCs. Organizations will be funded to develop detailed analysis
using modeling and simulation to study and evaluate defense capabilities (kinetic and non-kinetic) in the 2035 timeframe.

B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                FY 2025      FY 2026      FY 2027
FY 2026 Plans:
Conduct fully informed, high-fidelity modeling and simulation on emerging US capabilities against an overwhelming raid of
advanced mixed air and missile threats. Summarize impacts and lessons learned for senior decision-makers regarding layered
defense capabilities and extending defense durations and aircraft sortie generation rate. Finalize study that support the IAMD
Capability Portfolio Management Review. Initiate study that supports the Golden Dome for America.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue FY 2026 plans.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Minor programmatic adjustment.
